# {{projectName}}

A **Selenium + Java + TestNG** automation framework for **web** testing, with a **Page Object Model** structure and **{{reporter}}** reporting. Generated by QA Prism.

## Prerequisites
- JDK 11+ (`java -version`)
- Maven 3.8+ (`mvn -version`)
- Chrome installed (Selenium 4 auto-manages the driver binary)

## Setup
```bash
mvn clean install -DskipTests
```

## Running tests
```bash
mvn test                        # runs testng.xml
mvn test -Dtest=HomeTest        # single class
```
Set a different target site via the `WEB_BASE_URL` environment variable.

## Reports
- **Allure:** `mvn test` writes `allure-results/`; view with `allure serve allure-results`.
- **Extent:** the TestNG adapter writes a report under `test-output/` after the run.

## Structure
```
src/test/java/com/qaprism/
├── base/   BaseTest — WebDriver lifecycle
├── pages/  Page objects (POM) — BasePage + examples
└── tests/  TestNG test classes
pom.xml      Dependencies + Surefire (runs testng.xml)
testng.xml   Suite definition + reporter listener
```

## Conventions
- Page objects only — no `By` locators inside test classes.
- Prefer id / data-* locators over XPath.
- Driver setup lives in `BaseTest`, never in tests.

